# Lesson 5-1 — Circle Vocabulary and Basic Properties

## Today's Goals

* Identify and name the parts of a circle (radius, diameter, chord, secant, tangent, arc, sector, central angle)
* Compute arc length given a radius and central angle
* Compute the area of a sector
* Apply circle vocabulary to real-world contexts

---

## Vocabulary

* **circle** — the set of all points in a plane equidistant from a given point (the center)
* **radius** — a segment from the center to any point on the circle; length $r$
* **diameter** — a chord that passes through the center; length $d = 2r$
* **chord** — a segment whose endpoints both lie on the circle
* **secant** — a line that intersects the circle at two points
* **tangent** — a line that touches the circle at exactly one point (the point of tangency)
* **arc** — a portion of the circle between two points
* **minor arc** — an arc measuring less than 180°
* **major arc** — an arc measuring greater than 180°
* **semicircle** — an arc measuring exactly 180°
* **central angle** — an angle whose vertex is at the center of the circle
* **sector** — the region bounded by two radii and the arc between them

