## Explore: What Parts Make Up a Circle?

Imagine a bicycle wheel. The spokes connect the hub (center) to the rim (points on the circle). The tire traces the circle. A chord is like a shortcut across the wheel, and a tangent is a straight path that just grazes the edge without cutting through.

