## Learn: Parts of a Circle

### Key Concept: Radius and Diameter

The radius $r$ is the distance from the center to any point on the circle. The diameter $d$ is twice the radius:

$$d = 2r$$

### Key Concept: Arc Length

A central angle of $\theta°$ intercepts an arc that is a fraction $\frac{\theta}{360}$ of the full circumference $C = 2\pi r$:

$$\text{Arc length} = \frac{\theta}{360} \cdot 2\pi r$$

### Key Concept: Sector Area

The area of a sector with central angle $\theta°$ is the same fraction of the full area $A = \pi r^2$:

$$\text{Sector area} = \frac{\theta}{360} \cdot \pi r^2$$

