## Example 2 — Find Arc Length Given Radius and Central Angle

A circle has radius 10 cm. A central angle of 72° intercepts an arc. Find the arc length.

### Step 1: Write the Arc Length Formula

$$\text{Arc length} = \frac{\theta}{360} \cdot 2\pi r$$

### Step 2: Substitute Values

$$\text{Arc length} = \frac{72}{360} \cdot 2\pi(10)$$

$$= \frac{1}{5} \cdot 20\pi$$

$$= 4\pi$$

### Step 3: Compute the Approximate Value

$$4\pi \approx 12.57 \text{ cm}$$

✅ Answer: The arc length is $4\pi \approx 12.57$ cm.

---

## Example 3 — Find Sector Area

A circle has radius 6 inches. A central angle of 120° defines a sector. Find the area of the sector.

### Step 1: Write the Sector Area Formula

$$\text{Sector area} = \frac{\theta}{360} \cdot \pi r^2$$

### Step 2: Substitute Values

$$\text{Sector area} = \frac{120}{360} \cdot \pi(6)^2$$

$$= \frac{1}{3} \cdot 36\pi$$

$$= 12\pi$$

### Step 3: Compute the Approximate Value

$$12\pi \approx 37.70 \text{ in}^2$$

✅ Answer: The sector area is $12\pi \approx 37.70$ square inches.

---

## Example 4 — Relationship Between Radius and Diameter

A circular garden has a diameter of 14 feet. Find the radius, circumference, and area.

### Step 1: Find the Radius

$$r = \frac{d}{2} = \frac{14}{2} = 7 \text{ ft}$$

### Step 2: Find the Circumference

$$C = \pi d = 14\pi \approx 43.98 \text{ ft}$$

### Step 3: Find the Area

$$A = \pi r^2 = \pi(7)^2 = 49\pi \approx 153.94 \text{ ft}^2$$

✅ Answer: Radius = 7 ft, Circumference $= 14\pi \approx 43.98$ ft, Area $= 49\pi \approx 153.94$ ft².

